WEBVTT

00:10.789 --> 00:12.559
<i>(screaming)</i>

00:12.592 --> 00:13.561
<i>(screech)</i>

00:13.594 --> 00:15.397
There we go. That's it.

00:15.430 --> 00:16.634
(doorbell rings)

00:16.667 --> 00:18.370
Who is it?

00:18.403 --> 00:20.140
<i>NARRATOR:
In today's world,</i>

00:20.173 --> 00:22.445
<i>knowledge can mean
the difference between life</i>

00:22.478 --> 00:24.516
<i>-and tragedy.</i>
-(gasps)

00:24.549 --> 00:26.185
(screaming)

00:27.321 --> 00:28.423
<i>Introducing Aura...</i>

00:28.456 --> 00:29.492
♪ ♪

00:29.526 --> 00:31.530
<i>...your eye on the world.</i>

00:31.563 --> 00:34.736
<i>-The security
and peace of mind you deserve.</i>
-(chiming)

00:36.139 --> 00:37.809
<i>Delivery for Ms. Bryant.</i>

00:37.842 --> 00:39.546
WOMAN:
Oh, those are beautiful!

00:39.579 --> 00:41.416
I'm just cooking for my boys
right now.

00:41.449 --> 00:42.853
Could you please leave them
by the door for me?

00:42.886 --> 00:44.523
<i>-Sure thing.</i>
-Thank you so much.

00:44.556 --> 00:46.126
Have a lovely day.

00:46.159 --> 00:47.361
<i>NARRATOR:
Choose Aura.</i>

00:47.394 --> 00:48.531
-(chiming)
<i>-Now with powerful</i>

00:48.564 --> 00:50.635
<i>all-vision UltraSense technology</i>

00:50.668 --> 00:52.706
<i>that can see
what your eyes can't.</i>

00:52.739 --> 00:55.645
<i>So you'll always know
who's at the door.</i>

00:55.678 --> 00:56.780
(music ends)

00:58.617 --> 00:59.686
MAN:
It's cheap.

01:01.189 --> 01:02.793
Sorry?

01:02.826 --> 01:04.563
Price might look steep,

01:04.596 --> 01:05.799
but it's a bargain.

01:05.832 --> 01:08.203
-You have one?
-Best money I ever spent.

01:08.236 --> 01:11.242
Me and the wife
sleep like babies now.

01:12.612 --> 01:14.717
I don't know. It, uh...

01:14.750 --> 01:17.455
It... just seems
a little paranoid.

01:17.488 --> 01:19.459
Maybe 50 years ago. Back then,

01:19.492 --> 01:21.664
someone knocks
on your door after 6:00,

01:21.697 --> 01:23.835
"Hey! We got company.

01:23.868 --> 01:25.237
How nice."

01:25.270 --> 01:27.307
Nowadays, you hear that knock...

01:28.243 --> 01:30.915
...it's a maniac there
to cut your throat.

01:30.948 --> 01:33.286
♪ ♪

01:34.355 --> 01:36.325
(gate creaking)

01:39.465 --> 01:41.503
(brakes squeak softly)

01:54.730 --> 01:57.234
(sign creaking)

02:02.612 --> 02:04.148
(grunts softly)

02:07.354 --> 02:09.626
(opening box)

02:09.659 --> 02:11.564
Hey, honey.

02:11.597 --> 02:12.932
"Aura."

02:13.901 --> 02:15.237
What's this?

02:15.270 --> 02:16.774
Uh, um,

02:16.807 --> 02:18.210
you know,
with everything going on

02:18.243 --> 02:19.813
I just thought
it'd be a good idea.

02:19.846 --> 02:21.216
It was on sale.

02:21.249 --> 02:23.520
On sale for $200?

02:24.488 --> 02:25.558
They're popular now.

02:25.591 --> 02:28.230
Everyone has one.

02:28.263 --> 02:30.467
(sighs)

02:30.501 --> 02:33.941
Jaslyn, you wanted to move into
a gated community and we did.

02:33.974 --> 02:36.279
There's no crime here,
not even porch pirates.

02:36.312 --> 02:37.783
And you want to know why?

02:37.816 --> 02:40.421
We write a check
to the homeowners' association

02:40.454 --> 02:43.326
to pay for the security guards
out at the gate.

02:44.261 --> 02:46.534
Now, I get that you want to be
secure, but, at the same time...

02:46.567 --> 02:48.403
I really think
you just want me to feel guilty

02:48.436 --> 02:50.909
because I felt safer
moving out here.

02:50.942 --> 02:53.648
-Hang on...
-Sorry I have anxiety, okay?

02:53.681 --> 02:55.685
And I'm sorry it takes you
a little longer to get to work.

02:55.718 --> 02:58.724
I don't want you to feel guilty.

02:58.757 --> 03:00.562
I was just pointing out
that we're on a budget,

03:00.595 --> 03:03.332
and this is $200
that was not a part of the plan.

03:05.036 --> 03:06.574
I know. It...

03:06.607 --> 03:08.410
My store goes live this week,
okay?

03:08.443 --> 03:09.780
I can cover it.

03:09.813 --> 03:11.415
I'll get us back on the plan.

03:18.363 --> 03:20.968
Look, I'm sorry
if that sounded, uh...

03:28.851 --> 03:30.988
What happened to you as a kid...

03:32.792 --> 03:34.663
I can't imagine

03:34.696 --> 03:36.800
what that must have been like.

03:38.637 --> 03:41.442
But at the same time...

03:41.475 --> 03:44.482
I believe that there are two
types of people in this world--

03:44.516 --> 03:46.587
the ones that plan their lives

03:46.620 --> 03:48.791
-and the ones
who serve the ones...
-And the ones who serve the ones

03:48.824 --> 03:50.360
-that plans their lives.
-...that plan their lives.

03:50.393 --> 03:51.597
-That's right.
-Yes, I've heard it before.

03:51.630 --> 03:53.734
I don't need Tony Robbins.

03:53.767 --> 03:55.336
I need my husband.

03:56.305 --> 03:57.675
(chuckles)

03:59.078 --> 04:00.380
'Kay.

04:00.413 --> 04:02.017
I'm gonna go get my tool kit.

04:02.050 --> 04:03.453
Thank you.

04:06.727 --> 04:08.764
♪ ♪

04:12.404 --> 04:13.574
<i>(creaks)</i>

04:13.607 --> 04:15.377
(window slides open)

04:15.410 --> 04:17.481
(creaking)

04:27.334 --> 04:29.706
♪ ♪

04:33.112 --> 04:34.550
-(woman screams)
-MAN: Who the hell are you?!

04:34.583 --> 04:35.618
(gunshots)

04:35.651 --> 04:36.921
(hammering)

04:36.954 --> 04:38.690
(dog barking in distance)

04:40.561 --> 04:41.931
(chimes)

04:41.964 --> 04:44.335
(door creaking)

04:44.368 --> 04:46.405
♪ ♪

05:12.926 --> 05:15.430
♪ ♪

05:30.861 --> 05:31.963
<i>BRYCE:
Here we go.</i>

05:35.871 --> 05:37.609
Bryce, look, come here.
I sold something.

05:37.642 --> 05:39.044
-What? No.
-I sold something.

05:40.715 --> 05:42.050
-Ah.
-Yeah.

05:48.062 --> 05:49.900
What do you think?

05:49.933 --> 05:51.970
♪ ♪

05:54.876 --> 05:56.947
(whirring)

06:09.739 --> 06:11.744
(phone chiming)

06:11.777 --> 06:13.112
(grunts softly)

06:14.481 --> 06:15.818
(beeps)

06:17.087 --> 06:18.791
Can I help you?

06:18.824 --> 06:20.862
<i>Yeah, I'm here
for the home invasion.</i>

06:20.895 --> 06:22.999
<i>I was told it starts
around 3:00.</i>

06:25.170 --> 06:27.440
I asked you
to take it seriously.

06:28.510 --> 06:30.515
Well, did it work or not?

06:30.548 --> 06:33.754
Yes. A successful run-through.

06:33.787 --> 06:36.627
-Thank you.
-Uh-huh. Except for one thing.

06:36.660 --> 06:38.698
What?

06:38.731 --> 06:42.571
Never open the door
for a home invader.

06:44.241 --> 06:46.179
(screams, laughs)

06:46.212 --> 06:48.884
It's too late now. Don't you,
don't you run from me.

06:48.917 --> 06:51.623
Ooh, it's too late to run now.

06:51.656 --> 06:52.892
Ooh, I'm shaking.

06:52.925 --> 06:54.228
-Yeah, you better be.
-(chuckles)

06:54.261 --> 06:56.533
(phone alarm ringing)

06:58.069 --> 06:59.204
Shit.

07:01.008 --> 07:03.948
Almost forgot
I called a department meeting.

07:03.981 --> 07:06.920
-Tonight?
-Yeah, look, I told you
things would get crazy

07:06.953 --> 07:08.858
if I made supervisor.

07:08.891 --> 07:11.930
My team is a train wreck on
its way to being a clusterfuck.

07:11.963 --> 07:13.233
Cluttered workstations,

07:13.266 --> 07:15.103
outdated headers
on sales reports,

07:15.136 --> 07:17.676
emails written
in the wrong formats...

07:17.709 --> 07:20.548
-Well, that sounds like
the end of the world.
-(keys jingle)

07:20.581 --> 07:23.587
Yeah, and you sound like
the woman who I fired last week

07:23.620 --> 07:25.591
who said that I was OCD.

07:25.624 --> 07:28.531
Which, by the way, it's not OCD
to want things done correctly.

07:28.564 --> 07:30.535
-Okay.
-All right. Well, don't wait up.

07:30.568 --> 07:31.936
I'll try to be back soon.

07:33.139 --> 07:34.942
Bye.

07:44.629 --> 07:46.265
(notification chimes)

07:52.578 --> 07:55.216
-(sighs heavily) Fuck.
-(phone chiming)

08:01.195 --> 08:03.800
♪ ♪

08:17.294 --> 08:18.897
Hello?

08:26.947 --> 08:29.619
(quietly):
You're safe now.

08:32.658 --> 08:34.729
♪ ♪

08:39.772 --> 08:41.877
Hello?

08:41.910 --> 08:44.281
-(raccoon screeches)
-(gasps)

08:44.314 --> 08:45.751
(bottle rattles)

08:45.784 --> 08:47.354
Mm.

08:47.387 --> 08:49.892
(dog barks in distance)

09:01.348 --> 09:02.885
(phone chiming)

09:11.837 --> 09:13.641
<i>Hello, Jaslyn.</i>

09:13.674 --> 09:15.276
<i>Open the door.</i>

09:16.880 --> 09:18.651
What do you want?

09:18.684 --> 09:22.090
<i>I need to see you, Jaslyn.
Please, open the door.</i>

09:22.123 --> 09:26.265
I'm not opening anything.
You need to leave, okay?

09:26.298 --> 09:29.906
<i>-Let me in, Jaslyn.
Let me in now.</i>
-(banging)

09:29.939 --> 09:32.110
<i>Just open the door.</i>

09:32.143 --> 09:34.916
<i>You don't need to be afraid.</i>

09:34.949 --> 09:38.056
I'm-I'm calling the police
if you don't leave.

09:38.089 --> 09:40.661
The police have nothing to do
with this.

09:40.694 --> 09:42.331
<i>Please. It's cold out here.</i>

09:42.364 --> 09:43.934
<i>-Jaslyn.</i>
-(rattling)

09:45.403 --> 09:46.740
Please.

09:46.773 --> 09:48.009
I'm calling the cops
right now!

09:48.042 --> 09:49.345
-(banging on door)
-Open the door.

09:49.378 --> 09:51.415
(singsongy):
Jaslyn. Jaslyn...

09:51.448 --> 09:53.219
(line ringing)

09:53.252 --> 09:55.290
...open the door for me.

09:55.323 --> 09:57.394
Hello, hello. I-- No, you need
to send someone immediately.

09:57.427 --> 09:59.900
-Someone's trying to get
in my house.
-(singsongy): I'm not crazy...

09:59.933 --> 10:01.803
-They're trying to get in!
Please hurry!
-...just let me in,

10:01.836 --> 10:03.941
-Send someone right now!
-sweet Jaslyn.

10:03.974 --> 10:05.844
Please! He's getting in here!

10:08.382 --> 10:10.020
(tires screech)

10:10.053 --> 10:12.090
(indistinct chatter
over police radio)

10:15.163 --> 10:17.167
(quiet chatter)

10:17.200 --> 10:19.305
JASLYN:
No, I d-- I don't know
what he wanted.

10:19.338 --> 10:21.977
He-he wouldn't say.
He wouldn't say what he wanted.

10:22.010 --> 10:24.114
He just kept telling me
to let him in.

10:24.147 --> 10:25.718
And you're sure you've
never seen this man before?

10:25.751 --> 10:27.321
No, no. Not ever. No.

10:27.354 --> 10:28.791
-Oh, my God.
-Oh.

10:28.824 --> 10:30.160
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

10:30.193 --> 10:32.064
Thank God we installed
that stupid thing.

10:32.097 --> 10:33.867
Can you imagine
if you had opened the door?

10:33.900 --> 10:35.838
-I'm okay.
-(knocking)

10:35.871 --> 10:37.709
-Uh, knock, knock.
-Who are you?

10:37.742 --> 10:40.380
-Oh, I'm Hwan. I live next door.
-Yeah, no, he's...

10:40.413 --> 10:42.284
-He's cool. Come on in, Hwan.
-HWAN: Uh...

10:42.317 --> 10:45.257
Hey, guys, uh, I was talking
to Frank across the street

10:45.290 --> 10:46.860
who told me what happened...

10:46.893 --> 10:48.731
Freaky-deaky stuff.

10:48.764 --> 10:50.400
Anyway, I wanted you to know

10:50.433 --> 10:52.404
that I installed
a security camera

10:52.437 --> 10:54.041
over our garage last month.

10:54.074 --> 10:56.378
Pretty sure it has
a view of your front door.

10:57.949 --> 10:59.953
See there?
That's your front door.

10:59.986 --> 11:02.157
You said this dude showed up
an hour ago?

11:02.190 --> 11:04.461
-Yeah.
-Okay.

11:04.494 --> 11:06.967
This is an hour ago. Uh...

11:07.000 --> 11:08.269
I'll speed ahead.

11:12.043 --> 11:14.749
JASLYN:
Okay. That's me.

11:14.782 --> 11:18.723
The raccoon-- He-he was, he was
just like a little bit after.

11:25.971 --> 11:27.909
Wha... (stammers)

11:27.942 --> 11:31.482
-Is-is this the right recording?
-Uh, it's the only recording.

11:31.516 --> 11:35.056
BRYCE:
Well, there was the raccoon
and-and then the police, so...

11:35.089 --> 11:37.193
this must be the right video.

11:40.099 --> 11:42.237
I don't get it. Where is he?

11:42.270 --> 11:44.475
And you say the Aura app
didn't record anything, either?

11:44.509 --> 11:46.078
No. Nothing.

11:46.111 --> 11:47.815
Even though it's supposed to?

11:49.351 --> 11:51.088
Well, I didn't make this up.

11:51.121 --> 11:52.792
No one's saying you did.

11:52.825 --> 11:55.531
Is it possible you fell asleep
and had a bad dream?

11:55.564 --> 11:57.535
No! No, I know the difference

11:57.568 --> 12:00.073
between a dream and
something that really ha-- It...

12:00.106 --> 12:02.110
It wasn't a dream.
He was there.

12:02.143 --> 12:04.549
Well, ma'am, we have
a description of the man,

12:04.582 --> 12:06.352
which we can feed
into the system,

12:06.385 --> 12:09.491
see if it matches any
other cases, but beyond that,

12:09.525 --> 12:12.230
-there's not much more
we can do at this point.
-OTHER OFFICER: Best advice,

12:12.263 --> 12:15.069
keep your doors locked
and go on with your lives.

12:16.138 --> 12:18.843
If he comes back, call us.

12:23.553 --> 12:25.357
Uh...

12:25.390 --> 12:27.828
♪ ♪

12:30.299 --> 12:32.337
(insects chirping)

12:33.540 --> 12:35.510
(Bryce sighs)

12:36.880 --> 12:39.217
Listen, I don't want you
to bite my head off, but...

12:41.422 --> 12:44.562
I think the police may
have a point.

12:44.595 --> 12:47.535
You know, we're this new place,
you're starting a business,

12:47.568 --> 12:49.171
it's... it's a lot of stress.

12:49.204 --> 12:51.510
I'm wigging out
about my new position.

12:51.543 --> 12:53.514
That can't be helping,
and on top of it all,

12:53.547 --> 12:55.851
there's what happened to you
when you were a kid.

12:57.020 --> 12:59.291
(sighs)

12:59.324 --> 13:02.096
I just can't stop seeing him
in front of my bed.

13:02.631 --> 13:05.538
That fucking mask on.

13:05.571 --> 13:09.044
My parents tied up with
those ropes in their mouths.

13:09.077 --> 13:11.950
Hey, listen, I know
that it's not part of the plan,

13:11.983 --> 13:13.554
but if you want
to start seeing someone again,

13:13.587 --> 13:15.591
-we can totally make that work.
-I don't, I don't--

13:15.624 --> 13:18.296
I don't need to see someone.
I'm fine.

13:18.329 --> 13:19.933
Just had a bad night.

13:19.966 --> 13:22.103
So you agree then
that it was probably a dream.

13:23.072 --> 13:25.009
(sighs)

13:25.042 --> 13:26.580
I guess it had to be.

13:26.613 --> 13:27.981
Yeah.

13:29.184 --> 13:30.419
Okay.

13:32.123 --> 13:33.894
Good night.

13:33.927 --> 13:35.997
♪ ♪

13:46.185 --> 13:48.222
<i>ANNOUNCER (on TV):
Here's Williams
with a three-pointer,</i>

13:48.255 --> 13:50.193
<i>answering for Eastern...</i>

13:50.226 --> 13:52.565
(TV continues indistinctly)

13:52.598 --> 13:55.003
Hey, Jas, uh...

13:55.036 --> 13:57.106
You don't have to keep
checking the app.

13:58.275 --> 14:00.180
I thought I felt it ding.

14:00.213 --> 14:02.652
I thought maybe
the raccoon was back.

14:02.685 --> 14:04.388
Yeah, that is one home invader

14:04.421 --> 14:06.192
that you do not have
to worry about anymore.

14:06.225 --> 14:08.196
Why not?

14:08.229 --> 14:10.233
I put out some Bait Block
last week.

14:10.266 --> 14:13.139
It's supposed to work
for rats and mice,

14:13.172 --> 14:14.976
but it should work
for raccoons, too.

14:15.009 --> 14:17.447
-You poisoned him?
-Yeah, I poisoned him.

14:17.480 --> 14:19.519
A raccoon is basically
just like a big rat.

14:19.552 --> 14:22.057
Wha-- It was making a mess
everywhere.

14:22.090 --> 14:24.094
Not only here
but all around the neighborhood.

14:24.127 --> 14:26.265
Okay, so he made a mess.
He deserved to die?

14:26.298 --> 14:29.204
-He was really cute.
-I'm not the first person
on the planet

14:29.237 --> 14:31.576
-to kill a household pest.
-(phone chiming)

14:31.609 --> 14:35.016
-Maybe it didn't die.
-(chiming stops)

14:35.049 --> 14:37.353
(gasps)

14:40.627 --> 14:42.565
He's back.

14:42.598 --> 14:44.034
Who? The raccoon?

14:44.067 --> 14:45.370
Him.

14:45.403 --> 14:48.442
This is the guy.
That's him.

14:48.475 --> 14:50.714
Holy shit.

14:50.747 --> 14:52.484
-That's really him?
-Yeah.

14:52.518 --> 14:54.221
It wasn't a dream.

14:54.254 --> 14:55.958
Okay, okay. All right. Uh...

14:55.991 --> 14:57.595
-(phone beeps)
-Hey, man, uh...

14:57.628 --> 14:59.599
Wh-What are you,
what are you doing here?

14:59.632 --> 15:01.502
What do you want?

15:03.138 --> 15:06.011
-Hello?
<i>-Jaslyn.</i>

15:07.380 --> 15:09.619
<i>-Sweet Jaslyn.</i>
-(grunts)
-Hey, asshole.

15:09.652 --> 15:11.590
You better get the fuck
out of here.

15:11.623 --> 15:13.627
<i>Please open the door.</i>

15:13.660 --> 15:15.998
<i>I-I want to see Jaslyn.</i>

15:16.031 --> 15:18.737
<i>I need to see Jaslyn.</i>

15:18.770 --> 15:21.108
My sweet Jaslyn.

15:21.141 --> 15:22.612
-Okay.
-Where are you going?

15:22.645 --> 15:24.749
What are you doing?
Bryce, where are you going?

15:24.782 --> 15:26.553
Where do you think I'm going?
Stay here.

15:26.586 --> 15:29.324
What? Do not open--
Do not open the door.

15:29.357 --> 15:30.628
Stop!

15:30.661 --> 15:32.363
Something really weird
is happening.

15:36.706 --> 15:38.576
All right. Hold on.

15:39.545 --> 15:41.048
(phone keys beep)

15:41.081 --> 15:43.085
-(phone ringing)
-(crowd cheering on TV)

15:46.726 --> 15:48.429
-Hey.
<i>-BRYCE: Hey, Hwan.</i>

15:48.462 --> 15:50.200
Can you check
your security cameras?

15:50.233 --> 15:52.237
This asshole is back
outside of our house.

15:52.270 --> 15:54.207
One sec.

15:56.245 --> 15:57.347
Don't see anyone, man.

15:57.380 --> 15:58.550
<i>There's no one there.</i>

16:00.186 --> 16:02.692
-You sure?
-I'm staring at
your front door right now.

16:02.725 --> 16:04.629
It's unoccupied. (scoffs)
What's going on?

16:04.662 --> 16:06.533
<i>You guys okay, or what?</i>

16:06.566 --> 16:11.442
Uh... Yeah, no, no,
uh, we're fine.

16:11.475 --> 16:13.045
It's nothing.

16:15.383 --> 16:17.120
He says there's no one
out there.

16:17.153 --> 16:19.626
Why would you tell him that
we're fine when we're not?

16:19.659 --> 16:22.163
We need to call the police.

16:22.196 --> 16:23.600
The guy is...

16:25.136 --> 16:27.139
He's gone.

16:29.077 --> 16:30.681
Yeah. Fuck this.

16:30.714 --> 16:32.751
♪ ♪

16:41.234 --> 16:43.573
Son of a bitch.

16:46.411 --> 16:50.253
I know what this is.
Goddamn it.

16:50.286 --> 16:52.056
(Bryce sighs)

16:52.825 --> 16:54.461
Think about it.

16:54.494 --> 16:56.700
We only ever see this guy
over the app,

16:56.733 --> 16:58.770
-and the app is connected
to our Wi-Fi.
-So?

16:58.803 --> 17:00.541
(sighs heavily)

17:00.574 --> 17:03.847
So someone must've
hacked into it.

17:03.880 --> 17:05.751
It's a prank, Jas.

17:05.784 --> 17:07.855
Some basement-dwelling hacker
is doing this.

17:07.888 --> 17:09.726
No, when I was alone,

17:09.759 --> 17:12.364
I heard his voice come
through the door.

17:12.397 --> 17:15.069
The doorknob was turning.
How could it be hackers, Bryce?

17:15.102 --> 17:16.606
I don't know, Jas.

17:16.639 --> 17:19.444
It's the only explanation,
though. Think about it.

17:19.477 --> 17:21.716
I'm sure this happens to people
all the time.

17:21.749 --> 17:23.553
Google "Aura pranks," okay?

17:23.586 --> 17:25.557
I'm sure a bunch of shit
will come up.

17:25.590 --> 17:27.794
(chuckles):
This is the dumbest.

17:31.435 --> 17:33.472
♪ ♪

17:34.474 --> 17:35.577
<i>I'm not gonna hurt you.</i>

17:35.610 --> 17:37.447
<i>I'm just gonna tie you up,</i>

17:37.480 --> 17:39.117
<i>rape you and cut your head off
with a kitchen knife.</i>

17:39.150 --> 17:40.253
<i>That's all.</i>

17:40.286 --> 17:42.223
<i>Or maybe I'll kill you first.</i>

17:42.256 --> 17:45.496
<i>And then rape you,
cut you into little pieces.</i>

17:45.530 --> 17:47.434
(screams) Jesus, Bryce.

17:47.467 --> 17:50.373
(sighs) Good run today.
Got 15 miles in.

17:50.406 --> 17:52.110
What are you watching?

17:52.143 --> 17:54.716
Uh, I Googled "Aura pranks."

17:54.749 --> 17:57.320
<i>...and I'll just eat them</i>

17:57.353 --> 17:59.324
<i>one by one.</i>

17:59.357 --> 18:01.328
Sounds like a prank
if I ever heard one.

18:01.361 --> 18:04.134
Well, the woman that posted it
claims it's not a prank.

18:04.167 --> 18:05.838
She said that this guy just...

18:05.871 --> 18:07.608
He kept showing up on her Aura,

18:07.641 --> 18:09.679
and when they would
open the door, he'd be gone.

18:09.712 --> 18:12.384
Well, otherwise known
as a prank.

18:12.417 --> 18:14.321
They arrested someone
that looks just like him,

18:14.354 --> 18:16.526
and he was on
the sex offenders registry.

18:16.559 --> 18:18.830
Stop. Stop. Jas, listen to me.

18:18.863 --> 18:21.301
I rebooted the system.
I changed the passwords.

18:21.334 --> 18:24.374
I'll bet you a blow job you
don't have any more visitors.

18:24.407 --> 18:26.880
-Wow, Bryce.
-(chuckles): What? Okay, fine.

18:26.913 --> 18:28.617
I'll bet you something else.

18:28.650 --> 18:31.388
I've realized something
about the Aura guy--

18:31.421 --> 18:33.827
-our Aura guy.
-Okay.

18:33.860 --> 18:36.800
Okay, um...

18:36.833 --> 18:40.239
When I was at Jackson High,
we had this janitor,

18:40.272 --> 18:42.444
Mr. Hendricks.

18:42.477 --> 18:44.448
<i>He was pretty strange.</i>

18:44.481 --> 18:46.385
<i>He was always
talking to himself.</i>

18:46.418 --> 18:47.955
<i>I said hi to him once.</i>

18:47.988 --> 18:49.726
<i>You know, like,
"Good morning, Mr. Hendricks.</i>

18:49.759 --> 18:52.230
You look nice," trying to get
my friends to laugh.

18:52.263 --> 18:55.370
But he took me seriously.

18:55.403 --> 18:59.611
And then he was just kind of
all about me.

19:00.413 --> 19:03.419
<i>He was always looking at me
and smiling,</i>

19:03.452 --> 19:07.227
and he put candy in my locker.

19:07.260 --> 19:09.832
And he even polished my desk.

19:09.865 --> 19:13.372
<i>I used to find these love notes.</i>

19:13.405 --> 19:17.213
He would always sign it,
"To my sweet Jaslyn."

19:18.516 --> 19:20.319
<i>And then,</i>

19:20.352 --> 19:22.792
Mr. Hendricks was just gone.

19:22.825 --> 19:26.498
But then we heard a rumor
that he was in an institution.

19:26.532 --> 19:29.404
You don't think that's the guy
from the front door, do you?

19:29.437 --> 19:31.676
Bryce.

19:31.709 --> 19:34.649
"To my sweet Jaslyn."

19:34.682 --> 19:36.385
That doesn't sound familiar
to you?

19:36.418 --> 19:38.388
That's just like the guy
at our door.

19:39.725 --> 19:41.529
He even looked like Hendricks,
honestly.

19:41.562 --> 19:43.800
Uh, well, he couldn't've looked
that much like him.

19:43.833 --> 19:45.904
You just recognized him now.

19:45.937 --> 19:48.643
Well, it's been 20 years,
but I...

19:48.676 --> 19:50.514
-I'm sure it's him.
-Okay, Jas.

19:50.547 --> 19:53.954
Jas, just stop, please. Look.

19:53.987 --> 19:55.591
There's nobody really
at the door.

19:55.624 --> 19:57.862
So even if it looked
like Hendricks

19:57.895 --> 19:59.565
or sounded like Hendricks,

19:59.598 --> 20:02.805
it wasn't Hendricks
because it wasn't anybody.

20:02.838 --> 20:04.776
It was just a dumb prank.

20:04.809 --> 20:07.413
If you start obsessing
over this,

20:07.446 --> 20:08.683
it's just gonna mess up
your head,

20:08.716 --> 20:11.421
and it's gonna make you
go crazy.

20:11.454 --> 20:14.327
♪ ♪

20:14.360 --> 20:16.599
(chuckles softly) All right.

20:16.632 --> 20:18.536
I'm gonna go shower.

20:30.092 --> 20:32.731
(birds chirping)

20:36.037 --> 20:37.741
(sighs softly)

20:49.464 --> 20:51.702
(sighs)

20:58.482 --> 20:59.618
-Jas.
-(screams)

21:01.656 --> 21:03.693
(panting)

21:14.648 --> 21:16.852
♪ ♪

21:21.394 --> 21:23.465
(birds chirping)

21:33.686 --> 21:35.356
<i>JASLYN:
I'm so sorry to bother you
at home,</i>

21:35.389 --> 21:36.659
<i>but I couldn't find
a phone number.</i>

21:36.692 --> 21:38.797
My name is Jaslyn Taylor.

21:38.830 --> 21:42.638
I went to Jackson High when
your brother was working there.

21:42.671 --> 21:46.378
I'm arranging a reunion
for the Alumni Association,

21:46.411 --> 21:48.650
and I couldn't find
anything on him on the Internet

21:48.683 --> 21:51.890
or social media,
so I thought I'd take a chance

21:51.923 --> 21:53.727
and, uh,

21:53.760 --> 21:56.765
I was wondering if you could
point me in the right direction.

22:00.072 --> 22:03.112
I wanted your brother
to receive an invitation.

22:03.145 --> 22:06.552
A lot of the old staff
and alumni will be there,

22:06.585 --> 22:08.690
and I think that
they would love to see him.

22:08.723 --> 22:10.727
I know I would.

22:13.566 --> 22:15.469
Wish I could help you,

22:15.503 --> 22:17.808
but I don't know
where my brother is.

22:17.841 --> 22:19.010
Oh...

22:19.043 --> 22:22.083
Look, Dayle lived here

22:22.116 --> 22:24.855
ever since he lost the job
at the high school.

22:24.888 --> 22:27.060
And then a few months ago,
he took off.

22:27.093 --> 22:28.730
Didn't even say goodbye.

22:28.763 --> 22:30.634
So, you don't know
where he is now?

22:30.667 --> 22:32.838
Not a clue.

22:32.871 --> 22:35.042
It's not the first time
he's disappeared on me.

22:35.075 --> 22:36.879
I've gotten used to it.

22:36.912 --> 22:39.484
He's never really here
when he's here.

22:39.518 --> 22:42.591
It's probably the computers.

22:42.624 --> 22:45.530
He's into computers.

22:45.563 --> 22:47.433
Oh, all day and all night.

22:47.466 --> 22:50.072
He'd sit there hunched
with his headphones.

22:50.105 --> 22:53.111
A week would go by,
couldn't get a word out of him.

22:54.480 --> 22:56.451
You wouldn't happen to have
a recent picture of Dayle,

22:56.484 --> 22:57.888
would you?

22:57.921 --> 22:59.992
There's a book to go along
with the reunion,

23:00.025 --> 23:03.633
and there's a page
for staff and...

23:03.666 --> 23:05.503
it'd be great to include him.

23:08.643 --> 23:10.947
(floorboards creaking)

23:16.091 --> 23:18.128
♪ ♪

23:32.156 --> 23:34.728
MRS. HENDRICKS:
See what we got in here.

23:39.605 --> 23:42.911
You know,
you-you might look down there.

23:52.063 --> 23:55.168
♪ ♪

24:02.249 --> 24:05.757
-Is...
-That's all I got.

24:05.790 --> 24:08.428
Never was one for family photos.

24:12.169 --> 24:13.740
It's him. I'm sure of it.

24:13.773 --> 24:15.677
<i>BRYCE:
And this guy was a computer nut?</i>

24:15.710 --> 24:18.182
Of course he was the one
who hacked into the Aura.

24:18.215 --> 24:20.754
I cannot believe that this guy
is still obsessed with you.

24:20.787 --> 24:23.058
<i>I also can't believe
that you went to his house.</i>

24:23.091 --> 24:24.662
Yeah, I went to the house.

24:24.695 --> 24:26.031
I had to make sure
I wasn't crazy.

24:26.064 --> 24:28.035
Look, I'm gonna talk to patrol
tomorrow,

24:28.068 --> 24:29.538
and I'm gonna get them
up to speed on all this.

24:29.571 --> 24:30.741
<i>-Okay?</i>
-When you coming home?

24:30.774 --> 24:32.544
<i>I don't know, uh...</i>

24:32.577 --> 24:34.515
Not for at least another hour.

24:34.548 --> 24:36.084
Don't make anything for me,
okay?

24:36.117 --> 24:37.554
I'll pick up something
on the way home.

24:37.587 --> 24:39.991
<i>-I love you.</i>
-Love you, too.

24:44.233 --> 24:46.705
(phone chiming)

24:49.177 --> 24:51.783
♪ ♪

24:51.816 --> 24:54.086
<i>Open the door, Jaslyn.</i>

24:55.824 --> 24:58.563
<i>I know you're in there.
I have to see you.</i>

24:58.596 --> 25:01.769
<i>Please, Jaslyn. Open the door.</i>

25:01.802 --> 25:05.009
Mr. Hendr... (exhales)

25:05.042 --> 25:08.683
Dayle, what do you want?

25:08.716 --> 25:13.124
I want you to stop being afraid
of me and open the door.

25:17.601 --> 25:19.972
What will happen if I do that?

25:20.005 --> 25:23.178
DAYLE: I'll get to see you
again. That's all.

25:26.317 --> 25:27.821
That's all?

25:27.854 --> 25:30.259
(chuckles) That's all.

25:30.292 --> 25:32.329
♪ ♪

25:33.966 --> 25:36.003
(trembling breath)

25:43.653 --> 25:45.255
-(birds chirping)
-(dog barking in distance)

25:53.171 --> 25:55.208
♪ ♪

26:11.140 --> 26:12.611
(screaming)

26:12.644 --> 26:15.650
Thank you for letting me in,
Jaslyn.

26:15.683 --> 26:18.155
(breathing heavily)

26:18.188 --> 26:20.993
All you had to do was
open the door.

26:24.333 --> 26:27.373
But I'm sorry, I...

26:27.406 --> 26:29.812
I lied to you.

26:29.845 --> 26:32.651
(breathing heavily)

26:32.684 --> 26:35.188
-What was the lie?
-I'm...

26:36.859 --> 26:40.666
I'm not just here to see you.

26:42.403 --> 26:45.009
I want...

26:45.042 --> 26:47.346
more than that.

26:47.379 --> 26:49.250
(panting)

26:50.753 --> 26:52.190
What do you want?

26:52.223 --> 26:54.326
I want...

26:56.331 --> 26:57.768
I want...

26:57.801 --> 27:00.338
I want to...

27:04.781 --> 27:06.351
...to say I'm sorry.

27:06.384 --> 27:08.656
(trembling breath)

27:10.058 --> 27:11.696
You're sorry?

27:11.729 --> 27:15.169
For what I did to you
in high school. I...

27:15.202 --> 27:18.041
I convinced myself
that I loved you,

27:18.074 --> 27:22.918
and I-I... I didn't know
how to deal with that.

27:22.951 --> 27:27.794
I made you feel unsafe...

27:27.827 --> 27:30.165
and scared.

27:32.303 --> 27:36.277
I'm here to say I'm sorry.

27:38.916 --> 27:41.388
That's what you wanted?

27:41.421 --> 27:43.091
To say you're sorry?

27:43.124 --> 27:46.398
I'm not asking you
to forgive me.

27:46.431 --> 27:48.936
I just wanted you to hear me.

27:57.086 --> 27:58.388
Dayle.

28:01.127 --> 28:02.931
(sighs)

28:02.964 --> 28:06.404
I wasn't the greatest
in high school.

28:06.437 --> 28:08.275
My friends and I
made fun of you.

28:08.308 --> 28:12.182
We were... we were mean to you.

28:14.186 --> 28:15.890
I'm sorry.

28:22.069 --> 28:23.304
Maybe we can forgive each other.

28:24.908 --> 28:27.346
(chuckles)

28:27.379 --> 28:29.416
(laughs)

28:30.553 --> 28:33.792
♪ ♪

28:35.128 --> 28:37.199
(breathing heavily)

28:42.076 --> 28:44.313
(gasps)

28:47.486 --> 28:49.390
<i>ANCHORMAN:
And in other news,</i>

28:49.423 --> 28:51.227
<i>a missing person's case
has reached a sad conclusion.</i>

28:51.260 --> 28:54.868
<i>Dayle Hendricks had been missing
for just over two months.</i>

28:54.901 --> 28:57.340
<i>Police say his body was
discovered floating</i>

28:57.373 --> 28:59.410
<i>just south of the I-40 overpass,</i>

28:59.443 --> 29:01.014
<i>-where it's presumed
he took his own life.</i>
-(door opens)

29:01.047 --> 29:02.350
BRYCE:
Hello?

29:02.383 --> 29:04.120
JASLYN:
Hey.

29:04.153 --> 29:06.057
-What're you watching?
-Local news.

29:06.090 --> 29:08.796
-How was your day?
-It was good.

29:08.829 --> 29:11.902
Finally getting this department
in shape.

29:11.935 --> 29:14.908
You know, starting to get
with the plan.

29:14.941 --> 29:16.111
How about you?

29:16.144 --> 29:17.981
You have any more encounters?

29:18.014 --> 29:19.484
No.

29:19.518 --> 29:21.889
I guess you were right.
It was all quiet.

29:21.922 --> 29:23.893
Yeah, see that? Problem solved.

29:23.926 --> 29:26.164
Little reboot,
little change of password.

29:26.197 --> 29:28.903
-Little raccoon poison.
-(laughs)

29:28.936 --> 29:30.807
-I'm never gonna live this down,
huh?
-Never.

29:30.840 --> 29:33.445
What, I got to make a donation
to an animal shelter?

29:33.478 --> 29:36.017
-(phone chiming)
-That'd be nice, you murderer.

29:48.141 --> 29:50.547
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

29:50.580 --> 29:52.984
What is this now?

29:53.017 --> 29:54.521
<i>Please, I'm scared,</i>

29:54.554 --> 29:56.291
and I don't know where I am.

29:56.324 --> 29:57.561
JASLYN:
Who is this?

29:57.594 --> 30:00.432
Are you okay?
What happened to you?

30:00.465 --> 30:02.136
I was...

30:02.169 --> 30:05.209
I was at the-the park,
Grace Park,

30:05.242 --> 30:08.950
<i>and s-something happened,
I can't remember.</i>

30:08.983 --> 30:11.154
<i>I can't remember any more.
Please let me in.</i>

30:11.187 --> 30:12.958
<i>-Let me in.</i>
-You know what?
Enough of this shit.

30:12.991 --> 30:15.996
This ends here. Whoever's
doing this can fuck off.

30:17.934 --> 30:21.107
You can't you tell that
this is another goddamn prank?

30:21.140 --> 30:22.644
Hey. We're not playing
your goddamn game here.

30:22.677 --> 30:24.380
You understand me?

30:24.413 --> 30:26.217
Just die in whatever
fucking basement you live in.

30:26.250 --> 30:28.087
Oh, my God.
That is not how you...

30:29.423 --> 30:30.994
She's gone.

30:31.027 --> 30:33.933
-Wait, she's gone.
-She's gone.

30:33.966 --> 30:35.402
What are you doing?

30:35.435 --> 30:38.509
Killing our fucking warranty
is what I'm doing.

30:38.542 --> 30:40.547
Look, I know
you want to be safe,

30:40.580 --> 30:41.982
but you're gonna have to be okay

30:42.015 --> 30:43.920
with the security guards
out in the booth.

30:43.953 --> 30:46.023
♪ ♪

31:06.632 --> 31:09.303
(woman shouting indistinctly)

31:12.476 --> 31:14.514
(lively chatter in distance)

31:30.613 --> 31:32.683
♪ ♪

31:43.739 --> 31:45.976
(sighs)

31:49.651 --> 31:51.922
♪ ♪

32:03.344 --> 32:05.617
-We need to talk.
-Uh, yeah, sure.

32:05.650 --> 32:07.654
-Let me just finish reading--
-Finish it later.

32:11.394 --> 32:13.031
Okay.

32:13.064 --> 32:16.204
I drove out to Grace Park today.

32:16.237 --> 32:19.978
I happened upon a memorial
for Mary Jeane Burkett.

32:20.011 --> 32:21.515
I don't know who that is.

32:21.548 --> 32:24.353
She was killed in a hit-and-run.

32:24.386 --> 32:27.293
The driver was drunk,
and he's in prison for 15 years.

32:27.326 --> 32:29.665
Okay, uh, it's terrible.

32:29.698 --> 32:32.637
Um...
why're you telling me this?

32:32.670 --> 32:35.409
I'm telling you this
because Mary Jeane Burkett

32:35.442 --> 32:37.212
is who showed up
at our door yesterday.

32:38.314 --> 32:40.653
And I know
she didn't come here for me,

32:40.686 --> 32:42.456
so she must've come here
for you.

32:42.489 --> 32:46.665
Okay, why are we still talking
about the stupid video doorbell?

32:46.698 --> 32:49.003
I did some research
in the Aura chat rooms,

32:49.036 --> 32:50.305
and this has happened
to other people.

32:50.338 --> 32:53.311
There's a theory
that the new camera

32:53.344 --> 32:54.581
is...

32:54.614 --> 32:56.217
Okay, you know what?
Just watch this.

32:58.187 --> 33:00.760
<i>REVIEWER:
Now, try to stay with me.
These cameras use</i>

33:00.793 --> 33:02.597
<i>spontaneous parametric
down-conversion,</i>

33:02.630 --> 33:04.267
<i>which is a form
of quantum entanglement.</i>

33:04.300 --> 33:06.538
<i>That's why they can detect light
at only a few photons</i>

33:06.571 --> 33:08.509
<i>-per pixel.</i>
-What is this guy
even talking about?

33:08.542 --> 33:10.513
-Just listen.
<i>-Some people say that,
by punching</i>

33:10.546 --> 33:12.116
<i>into the quantum realm,</i>

33:12.149 --> 33:14.521
<i>these babies act
as a magnet for spirits.</i>

33:14.554 --> 33:16.257
<i>That's right.</i>

33:16.290 --> 33:17.627
<i>-The dead.
-(screaming)</i>

33:17.660 --> 33:19.631
<i>And if you watch
any ghost hunting shows,</i>

33:19.664 --> 33:22.369
<i>you know ghosts are basically
electromagnetic fields.</i>

33:22.402 --> 33:24.407
<i>That's why you see these hunters
running around</i>

33:24.440 --> 33:26.244
<i>with their EMF detectors.</i>

33:26.277 --> 33:29.518
<i>And that, my friends,
is exactly what the Aura is.</i>

33:29.551 --> 33:30.686
(Bryce laughing)

33:31.688 --> 33:33.325
I mean, come on.

33:33.358 --> 33:34.293
(chuckles)

33:34.326 --> 33:36.464
Ghosts and ghost meters?

33:36.497 --> 33:39.170
Is anything this guy's saying
supposed to make sense?

33:39.203 --> 33:40.607
The other day, when you asked

33:40.640 --> 33:42.677
if there was any more activity
on the Aura,

33:42.710 --> 33:44.413
I said no.

33:44.446 --> 33:45.617
I lied to you.

33:45.650 --> 33:48.288
Mr. Hendricks came back.

33:48.321 --> 33:50.526
And I let him in.

33:50.559 --> 33:52.763
Oh, Jas, come on.

33:53.732 --> 33:55.135
You did what?

33:55.168 --> 33:57.607
He didn't want to hurt me.

33:57.640 --> 33:59.711
He just wanted to apologize.

34:01.548 --> 34:02.517
D...

34:02.550 --> 34:04.153
He just wanted to apologize?

34:04.186 --> 34:05.155
-I don't...
-Yeah.

34:05.188 --> 34:06.424
Just that.

34:06.457 --> 34:07.493
Just sorry.

34:07.527 --> 34:09.229
Okay.

34:10.498 --> 34:12.369
So if that's...

34:12.402 --> 34:14.340
if that's what did happen,

34:14.373 --> 34:15.743
um...

34:15.776 --> 34:17.514
why, then...

34:17.547 --> 34:19.450
are we talking about ghosts?

34:19.483 --> 34:22.557
Because Mr. Hendricks
was already dead when he came.

34:22.590 --> 34:24.459
He jumped in a river weeks ago.

34:26.297 --> 34:29.538
Look, Mr. Hendricks
came here for a reason.

34:29.571 --> 34:31.341
And so did Mary Jeane Burkett.

34:31.374 --> 34:33.713
And you need to tell me
what that reason is.

34:33.746 --> 34:35.182
I don't know.

34:35.215 --> 34:37.486
You didn't kill her,

34:37.520 --> 34:38.756
so what does she want with you?

34:38.789 --> 34:40.158
I don't know, Jas.

34:40.191 --> 34:41.361
I don't know who she is

34:41.394 --> 34:42.697
and I don't believe in ghosts

34:42.730 --> 34:44.901
and I really can't believe
that you do.

34:44.934 --> 34:48.141
And it is
so utterly disappointing

34:48.174 --> 34:50.278
that you would let this
disrupt our lives.

34:51.480 --> 34:54.286
(chiming)

34:55.321 --> 34:56.390
What was that?

34:59.263 --> 35:00.365
She's back.

35:02.369 --> 35:05.208
I fished the Aura out
of the trash and I put it back.

35:05.241 --> 35:06.812
It's cracked,
but it still works.

35:06.845 --> 35:08.516
<i>Hello?</i>

35:08.549 --> 35:09.918
<i>Please open the door.</i>

35:09.951 --> 35:11.689
-Bryce, what does she want?
-(door rattling)

35:11.722 --> 35:13.157
I don't-- I don't know.

35:13.959 --> 35:15.897
You don't know?

35:15.930 --> 35:18.602
-Okay, I'll ask her then.
-I don't-- I don't know
what she wants!

35:18.635 --> 35:19.905
-(pounding, rattling)
-Who is she?
-I don't know

35:19.938 --> 35:21.608
what she wants.
I don't know who she is.

35:21.641 --> 35:24.915
Who the fuck
is Mary Jeane Burkett?!

35:24.948 --> 35:26.752
Oh, my God. I don't know!
(stammers)

35:26.785 --> 35:29.456
She was my fiancée!

35:31.293 --> 35:32.495
I'm sorry.

35:38.776 --> 35:41.681
I should've told you sooner,
but I just...

35:43.384 --> 35:44.787
I never had the words.

35:46.558 --> 35:48.796
The night that she was killed,
we were at the park.

35:48.829 --> 35:50.264
It was a place we liked to go.

35:51.267 --> 35:52.837
<i>That's where I broke it off.</i>

35:52.870 --> 35:55.441
<i>There were probably
a million reasons, but...</i>

35:56.377 --> 35:57.847
I just wasn't ready.

35:57.880 --> 35:59.584
<i>I didn't think she was the one.</i>

35:59.617 --> 36:00.853
<i>She got angry.</i>

36:00.886 --> 36:02.957
<i>She told me
she never wanted to see me again</i>

36:02.990 --> 36:05.462
and that she would walk home.

36:05.495 --> 36:06.765
(tires screech)

36:06.798 --> 36:08.268
<i>So I left. I drove away.</i>

36:08.301 --> 36:10.439
♪ ♪

36:10.472 --> 36:13.445
<i>It haunts me every day.</i>

36:13.478 --> 36:15.850
And I know-- and-and I know
it doesn't seem that way

36:15.883 --> 36:18.321
because I do a good job
of holding it all in,

36:18.354 --> 36:19.691
but-but...

36:19.724 --> 36:20.993
it does, Jas.

36:21.026 --> 36:22.864
She probably just wants
to forgive you.

36:22.897 --> 36:24.366
She probably wants to tell you
that it's not your fault.

36:24.399 --> 36:26.237
I don't think so.

36:26.270 --> 36:27.640
(door rattling)

36:27.673 --> 36:30.613
<i>Please, Bryce.
Please, let me in.</i>

36:30.646 --> 36:32.517
-(rattling)
<i>-Bryce,</i>

36:32.550 --> 36:34.286
<i>-don't be afraid.</i>
-(pounding)

36:34.319 --> 36:36.023
-(rattling)
-(sighs)

36:36.056 --> 36:38.995
-Bryce, we need to find out
what she wants.
-(pounding)

36:44.607 --> 36:46.678
(crickets chirping)

36:48.615 --> 36:50.619
(wind blows)

36:52.322 --> 36:54.260
(door closes)

36:54.293 --> 36:55.696
She gone?

36:55.729 --> 36:57.567
No, Bryce,

36:57.600 --> 36:59.469
she's not.

37:02.944 --> 37:04.380
MARY JEANE:
Look at him, Bryce.

37:04.413 --> 37:06.918
He was gonna be your son.

37:08.321 --> 37:10.859
What is she talking about,
Bryce?

37:11.895 --> 37:13.331
MARY JEANE:
Tell her, Bryce.

37:13.364 --> 37:14.667
Tell her the truth.

37:16.972 --> 37:19.409
(Bryce sighs deeply)

37:20.579 --> 37:22.415
Oh, man. I'm tired.

37:24.353 --> 37:26.423
♪ ♪

37:33.672 --> 37:35.374
She was pregnant.

37:36.978 --> 37:38.515
What was I supposed to do?

37:42.990 --> 37:44.928
Couldn't let that happen.

37:44.961 --> 37:46.030
-Neither one of us!
-Why are you fucking yelling
at me?!

37:46.063 --> 37:48.101
-Get rid of it!
-Stop it, Bryce!

37:48.134 --> 37:49.938
-Where are you going?
-Can't fucking do this.
Where am I going?!

37:49.971 --> 37:51.775
-I don't know...
-Wait, where are you going?

37:51.808 --> 37:53.478
-Stop.
-What are you doing?!
Why are you holding me so tight?

37:53.512 --> 37:55.348
-We need to end this. Now.
-We need to end what?

37:55.381 --> 37:57.319
-Bryce, you're hurting me! Stop.
-Stop! Enough! En...

37:57.352 --> 38:00.592
(tires screeching)

38:05.769 --> 38:08.007
-(engine revving)
-(tires screeching)

38:17.560 --> 38:19.630
♪ ♪

38:28.982 --> 38:30.418
Help!

38:30.451 --> 38:31.955
(Mary Jeane gasping softly)

38:31.988 --> 38:34.460
-Help!
-MARY JEANE (weakly):
Please, baby.

38:34.493 --> 38:36.565
Help me. Help me.

38:36.598 --> 38:37.967
Help.

38:38.000 --> 38:39.570
(crying)

38:41.508 --> 38:43.043
Bryce. (gasping)

38:45.081 --> 38:46.785
Help. Help.

38:46.818 --> 38:48.421
(gasping)
Help, Bry...

38:48.454 --> 38:50.025
(pained gasping)

38:50.058 --> 38:51.762
Help.
(exhales)

38:51.795 --> 38:54.400
(gasping rapidly)

38:54.433 --> 38:56.170
Please, baby.

38:56.203 --> 38:57.740
Help me. Help me.

38:57.773 --> 38:59.678
(gasping)

39:03.417 --> 39:04.386
Help.

39:04.419 --> 39:05.556
Bryce.

39:05.589 --> 39:06.891
(whimpers softly)

39:08.528 --> 39:10.464
-(sighs)
-(gasping rapidly)

39:16.210 --> 39:19.482
Shh. It's okay, it's okay.
I'm sorry.

39:23.124 --> 39:24.092
-(snap)
-(gasps)

39:26.196 --> 39:28.602
♪ ♪

39:39.590 --> 39:41.460
It was a baby, Jas.

39:42.530 --> 39:43.599
(scoffs)

39:43.632 --> 39:45.703
I couldn't allow that.

39:45.736 --> 39:47.539
Wasn't in the plan.

39:49.844 --> 39:51.079
(sniffles)

39:52.115 --> 39:53.786
Oh.

39:53.819 --> 39:55.923
(sighs)

39:55.956 --> 39:57.125
And now neither are you.

39:57.158 --> 39:59.096
(breathing heavily)

39:59.129 --> 40:00.866
(gasps)

40:00.899 --> 40:03.772
-(choking)
-(poker clatters)

40:04.741 --> 40:06.878
(wheezing)

40:06.911 --> 40:09.049
(grunts, groans)

40:09.082 --> 40:11.020
(exhales, groans)

40:11.053 --> 40:12.089
(gasping)

40:12.122 --> 40:14.093
(thud)

40:14.126 --> 40:15.629
(choking)

40:15.662 --> 40:17.667
(groans, gasping)

40:17.700 --> 40:19.470
-JASLYN: You're right, Bryce.
-(choking)

40:19.504 --> 40:21.007
She's not here to forgive you.

40:21.040 --> 40:22.576
(Bryce gasping)

40:30.793 --> 40:32.830
♪ ♪

40:38.107 --> 40:40.144
♪ ♪

40:41.614 --> 40:43.017
(insects trilling)

40:43.050 --> 40:44.486
<i>BUILDING MANAGER:
Okay.</i>

40:44.520 --> 40:46.223
You're right
about the thermostat.

40:46.256 --> 40:48.027
-Mm.
-I'll get a repairman up here
first thing tomorrow.

40:48.060 --> 40:50.098
-Wonderful.
-By the way,

40:50.131 --> 40:52.169
I took the liberty
of installing your Aura

40:52.202 --> 40:53.772
before I came in.

40:53.805 --> 40:55.643
I didn't ask you for that.

40:55.676 --> 40:56.778
Everyone in the building
gets 'em.

40:56.811 --> 40:58.615
It's in the contract.

40:58.648 --> 41:00.919
Keeps the insurance rates down.

41:04.694 --> 41:06.631
♪ ♪

41:13.177 --> 41:15.916
(chiming)

41:17.686 --> 41:19.924
(chiming continues)

41:26.003 --> 41:27.906
♪ ♪

41:30.946 --> 41:32.182
<i>Hey, Jas?</i>

41:32.215 --> 41:35.054
<i>Open the door, Jas. It's me.</i>

41:35.087 --> 41:36.925
<i>Look, I know--
I know you're in there.</i>

41:36.958 --> 41:39.029
<i>I just want to talk,
so let me in.</i>

41:39.062 --> 41:40.733
Fuck off, Bryce!

41:40.766 --> 41:42.202
<i>Oh, I can't do that.</i>

41:42.235 --> 41:43.939
<i>Just want to have a word
with my wife.</i>

41:43.972 --> 41:45.976
<i>We need to talk about the plan.</i>

41:48.849 --> 41:50.853
<i>Let me the fuck in, Jas!</i>

41:50.886 --> 41:52.557
<i>-Let me the fuck in!</i>
-(rattling)

41:52.590 --> 41:53.692
-(pounding)
<i>-Open the door!</i>

41:53.725 --> 41:55.195
<i>You're my fucking wife!</i>

41:55.228 --> 41:56.330
<i>You answer to me!</i>

41:56.363 --> 41:57.600
<i>You'll never get away from me!</i>

41:57.633 --> 41:59.604
<i>You understand me?! Never!</i>

41:59.637 --> 42:01.073
<i>Open the fucking door!</i>

42:01.106 --> 42:02.910
<i>Jaslyn!</i>

43:14.887 --> 43:15.922
